Not content to use in the text even several times the expression "as in Iraq", he did not hesitate, what is more, to use the title of the Bush speech of January 2007 as the title of his own speech: "A new road forward"
At the same time, he personally criticized Bush's idea of sending new reinforcements into an Iraq consumed by civil war as "irresponsible and catastrophic decision in its consequences."
The following months, however, showed that the Bush strategy, which emanated from the recommendations of the campaign commanders, was the only possible and likely to be successful at such a point that the newspapers at present do not speak at all of Iraq.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, that said, objectively speaking, he left his successor a far more favourable final situation than one could hope.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan, the miracle will reproduce
It is again the campaign commanders who called for an increase in the military contingent, including the commander of the Afghan operation, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the reluctance of the White House despite the habits of subordination.
He asked for 40,000 men to be able to make the situation more favourable.
The president hesitated for three months, but if there was no better option, he had at least crushed the general of 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to remove the promise of an additional 5,000 from Europe, even though he had 10,000 originally.
What brings the most problems throughout Obama's strategy seems to be his intention to remove the armies of Afghanistan in 18 months' time and complete this process in three years' time. Obama's entire doctrine brings more questions than it provides answers.
Many doubt that an increase of half will bring the same fruits as progress in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honour the agreements.
The Afghan situation stands out by the exact opposite - no one can be counted and no treaty is respected.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, accustomed to changing leaders on a daily basis according to what arranges them.
Political institutions, although officially founded, will remain only powder in the eyes behind which will proliferate patriarchal ethnic relations.
It is particularly complex to balance the interests of the various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity in relation to relations, which are still complicated by the Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "prompt state to act", which is the basic purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The temporal horizon of Obama's strategy is perplexed by his voluntarism.
In the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only worsened and is currently on the verge of chaos.
Only a heart purely romantic and out of reality can be persuaded that the small soldiers sent in the tumult of war in view of their "soon return home" will bring there a true miracle.
From a political point of view, defining a date for the withdrawal of troops is merely irresponsible, as the Taliban will consider it to be the indirect admission of the American defeat.
The latest NATO summit has shown that the will of Europeans to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is negative.
European policies do not know or want to explain to their voters how security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the mountains of the Hindu Kush.
Another factor capable of radically altering the situation is the evolution of Iran-related events.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the sanctions strengthened have no effect on Iranians, the Americans will face the very difficult issue of a resolution of the problem through the use of military force.
For example, it will be necessary to respond to this when, according to Obama, America will come to the victorious withdrawal of the troops from Afghanistan.
However, each such solution will result in a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only shame for Obama is that it remains three years until the presidential elections and therefore there is still enough time for him to plan on a new strategy, in case it turns out to be a total fiasco.
