Four-step garage currency
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user obtains a quote in only four steps: identify the vehicle, look for the spare part, create a quote and generate it.
The ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially in order to convince older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 passenger cars, 109 all-terrains, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it, a computer and Internet connection are needed.
Once the model to be repaired is identified by its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary piece is selected.
The user may include variables such as labour price, increases or reductions, and then print the quote to return it to the customer.
AudaTaller is not an estimation tool like AudaPlus, but a reference catalogue.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one for garages does not include estimated working time.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be credited.
